  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Generally, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the economy as seemingly legitimate assets\n\nLegal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize intentional efforts to hide the origins of money gained from criminal activities.",
